revision.text: {{also|YAF|»ùaf}} ==Middle English== ===Verb=== {{head|enm|verb form}} # [[gave]] #* Chaucer #*: He '''yaf''' hym yiftes preciouse and deere. #* '''c. 1471''', ''An English Chronicle, 1377-1461'': #*: there the erl of Dunbar becam his manne, and the kyng '''yaf''' him the Counte of Richemunde.
